    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like i'm a ghost haunting my own life. if there's no \"me\" left to experience anything, then the idea of \"rediscovering\" something feels like a joke. it's just more pretending. i look at the world and it feels like it's happening to someone else, and there's no reason for this empty version of me to keep dragging this around. it doesn't feel like i'm living, i'm just... persisting. and it's exhausting.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Feeling like a ghost persisting through life is an incredibly heavy and isolating burden to carry. The exhaustion you describe is a direct result of masking so much pain and emptiness. While the idea of \"rediscovering\" can feel too grand right now, a smaller step might be gentle self-compassion for simply persisting through this difficult time. Talking to a therapist can help you explore the exhaustion and find a more tolerable way of being in this moment.",
      "source": "target",
